                    app:layout_constraintRight_toRightOf="parent"
                    android:text="Physics is the study of the fundamental laws of nature. Applied physics uses these laws to understand phenomena that have practical applications. Engineering in turn makes use of these phenomena for human purposes. Engineering physics thus forms a link between the fundamental laws of nature and their applications. The Engineering Physics program is oriented towards students who are stimulated by the challenge of solving technical problems ranging from the fundamental to the applied, and who are seeking a broadly-based engineering education to prepare for diverse careers in a rapidly changing technical world. Engineering Physics focuses on the fundamentals of physics and mathematics; both experimental and theoretical that is at the heart of modern engineering and science and has broad applicability. By choosing a particular concentration, you can combine this physics base with a firm background in a conventional area of engineering or applied science. Engineering Physics emphasizes the basic physics underlying most engineering developments, and mathematical tools vital to all engineers and scientists. The Engineering Physics curriculum encourages students to extend themselves and develop broad skills in the physical sciences."/>
